claim: KFC was taken over by the R.J. Reynolds food and tobacco mirror.
premise_source_doc_sentence: In the early-1970s , KFC was sold to the spirits distributor Heublein , which was taken over by the R.J. Reynolds food and tobacco conglomerate ; that company sold the chain to PepsiCo .
